# Trivy IaC ignore file — https://trivy.dev/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/
# Wired into CI via the `trivyignores` input in .github/workflows/security.yml.

# AWS-0132 (HIGH): "Bucket does not encrypt data with a customer managed key." The S3 module (modules/s3) deliberately uses SSE-S3 (AES256). This is an intentional default for the boilerplate: buckets are still encrypted at rest, and SSE-KMS is not supported for the S3 server-access-log destination bucket
AWS-0132

# AWS-0031 (HIGH): "ECR image tags shouldn't be mutable." The ECR repos use IMMUTABLE_WITH_EXCLUSION so content tags (git SHA / v* releases, i.e. what actually gets pinned into the running Lambda) are immutable, while only `latest*` stays mutable — the deploy pipeline re-pushes `latest` as its bootstrap sentinel (terraform-ecr-check) and Lambda baseline image_uri. Trivy's adapter only maps the bare "IMMUTABLE" value to immutable, so it still flags the exclusion variant; suppressed here since the exposure is limited to the intentionally-floating `latest` tag.
AWS-0031
